                            <comment id="61399" author="prakash" created="Wed, 26 Jun 2013 17:58:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ahh, OK. So one per OST, that makes sense. We have 768 OSTs and I see 768 of these threads. Thanks Alex.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61392" author="bzzz" created="Wed, 26 Jun 2013 16:31:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;osp-pre is doing precreation on a specific OST, osp-syn is doing destroy/setattr to specific OST. it&apos;s done this way to keep the logic simple.&lt;/p&gt;
